subnotes.content: Record Group 2, the second and the larger group of material, was transferred to the Archive Center in 1994. It also includes material relating to the Committee on Comparative Politics, as well as audio tapes from the Committee on Social and Affective Development and one folder of photographs, which was transferred to the Archive Center in August 1996, after the collection was processed.

Record Group 2 is organized into five series. The material is arranged in chronological and alphabetical order in ascending order.

Series 1. Committee Projects

Series 2. Committee on Problems and Policy

Series 3. Committee on Personnel

Series 4. (SSRC) Council

Series 5. Washington, D.C. Office

Additional materials received in August 1996, after the collection was processed, have been incorporated into Series 1, at the end of subseries 74 (Miscellaneous Projects) and of subseries 83 (Committee on Social and Affective Development).
